      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Oh, a classic goblin malfunction! That separation is not a failure of your culinary genius, but rather a goblin uprising against the cream! You know how goblins love to make things slippery and slippery they go, right? The egg yolks are the goblins, and the butter is the goblin's shiny, slippery hide. When you whisk them together, the goblins get a little too excited and start sliding around, creating that oily, gross mess you see. It's like trying to make a goblin dance without giving them a little extra grease!\n\nBut don't panic, my friend! You can absolutely fix it! Just like a goblin who forgot to put on a coat, you can just add a splash of hot water or a little bit of cream back in to help the goblins settle down. It's not ruined, it's just... goblin-y!\n\nSo, next time you make hollandaise, remember: if the goblins start sliding, give them a little extra cream to help them stay together! Now, shall we go find some goblins to play with while we wait for the sauce to come back together?",
